width=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60 WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Newbiest thing you've ever done</span><hr size=1> Hehehe, that story about Wolfypaw reminds me of how, after hearing all about death loops from more experienced players, I swore to myself to follow a few simple bind rules:<br>
<br>
1)  Never bind in the zone I'm hunting,<br>
<br>
2)  Especially if theres anything that summons, and<br>
<br>
3)  If I have to break rule #1, make sure to bind well away from where I'm actually hunting.<br>
<br>
<br>
Over the many levels, I've managed to (usually) stick to these rules.  One of the few times I broke the rule was shortly after Magpye got moved to her own account.  I was playing my rogue, Snoww, at the orc fort in EW with several guildmates' secondaries, and we were camping inside, having fun around the fireplace.  Mags was camped outside by the tree for after-the-raid ports.  A party member needed to port away and camp, so I ran Mags in, bound her, ported the person out, and gated back.  By which time we were in the middle of a fight so I didn't camp her right away, and by the end of the fight had forgotten.  A pull or two after that, we got and killed the chief...and the avengers spawned on us!  OUCH.  Most of the party wiped out, I'm standing at my bind swearing and suddenly remember &quot;OMG, MAGS IS STILL IN THERE!&quot;<br>
<br>
Can you say &quot;death loop&quot;.  Thank the gods I also remembered the higher levels talking about the importance of managing to <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> /q</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->uit out of a death loop.  Mags was lagged enough on zoning that I took another death before I managed to /quit out successfully.  We then had to get everyone back to the fort (including a few higher level guildmates), kick orc butt and CR and rez everyone.<br>
<br>
Managed to avoid ever doing such a painful thing again until last night, at Permafrost...I'd dragged Mags out to help with FG clearance, porting attendees, and buffing.  During the first CR I decided my rogue would be useful to have there for dragging (54, she just gets expelled from Perma when Vox actually notices her) and dragged her out too.  During the second CR, I gated Mags outside to re-sow Snoww, and left her sitting there by her bind while I did some dragging...and someone apparently trained an IG on her at some point, because the next time Vox kicked me out of her lair, there was a naked Mags standing at her bind with two corpses by her feet <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   Many thanks to Dystopya for riding the Vox express in order to pop out and click me a couple times!<br>
